      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MORE TROUBLE (1) switched yards and was quickly back on track, beaten a whisker over 1609m at Townsville. Has plenty of weight, but he'd been performing well in metro and provincial company and a top hoop sticks board. The extra metres should suit, and he can go one better. KAYLEEN'S PROFIT (5) has been racing well in decent contests at Rockhampton. Missed 1L there this trip three back and gets her chance to record an overdue success. BO BO BEWARE (3) deserved his 62 win over 1600m at Rockhampton, beating the above home. Has won over this distance and has the inside gate. A chance again. KINGS CASTLE (4) resumed from a spell over 1400m at Townsville, beaten 3 lengths. Races well over this longer distance, and Ryan Wiggins is a key engagement. Fitter this time and consider in a suitable race.",
